[2026-03-19T08:28:53.697Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Execute this requirement immediately without asking questions.\n\n## REQUIREMENT\n\n# Replace silent catch blocks with contextual error logs\n\n## Metadata\n- **Category**: code_quality\n- **Effort**: Medium (2/3)\n- **Impact**: Unknown (7/3)\n- **Scan Type**: observability_scout\n- **Generated**: 3/18/2026, 7:37:59 PM\n\n## Description\nThe dispatcher.ts file contains at least 5 catch blocks that silently swallow errors with best effort comments. Replace each with a logger.error call that includes the executionId and the operation that failed. This preserves the non-throwing behavior while making DB write failures visible to operators.\n\n## Reasoning\nSilent catch blocks are observability black holes. If the SQLite database becomes locked or corrupted, these swallowed errors mean the system silently loses execution data with zero indication. This is a low-effort fix with high diagnostic value.\n\n\n## Recommended Skills\n\nUse Claude Code skills as appropriate for implementation guidance. Check `.claude/skills/` directory for available skills.\n\n## Notes\n\nThis requirement was generated from an AI-evaluated project idea. No specific goal is associated with this idea.\n\n## DURING IMPLEMENTATION\n\n- Use `get_memory` MCP tool when you encounter unfamiliar code or need context about patterns/files\n- Use `report_progress` MCP tool at each major phase (analyzing, planning, implementing, testing, validating)\n- Use `get_related_tasks` MCP tool before modifying shared files to check for parallel task conflicts\n\n## AFTER IMPLEMENTATION\n\n1. Log your implementation using the `log_implementation` MCP tool with:\n   - requirementName: the requirement filename (without .md)\n   - title: 2-6 word summary\n   - overview: 1-2 paragraphs describing what was done\n   - category: one of feature/bugfix/refactor/performance/security/infrastructure/ui/docs/test\n   - patternsApplied: comma-separated patterns used (e.g. \"repository pattern, debounce, memoization\")\n\n2. Verify: `npx tsc --noEmit` (fix any type errors)\n\nBegin implementation now."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"55675ad4-950c-4582-8f74-f4aefa7e14ad","uuid":"eea53126-a305-4d46-8667-7f6a926ab103","timestamp":"2026-03-19T08:28:53.615Z","isSynthetic":true}
